Lagos 57 Media Group, an independent communication agency, has concluded plans to unveil ‘Lagos Show Podcast,’ a medium through which Governor Babajide Sanwo–Olu’s administration and the presidential ambition of former Lagos State Governor Bola Tinubu would be interrogated and x-rayed by the people, experts and analysts. The platform is a digital audio assessment of the governor’s administration since he took over leadership. Project Director Adesina Kasali said Lagos 57 Media was apolitical and driven by the tenets of democracy, which entails holding leaders accountable for their actions  and assessing the impacts of such on the people.   2023: ‘Zoning good, but competence better’     Council to go after debtors     Mamora, others condole with Adediran’s family   “In line with this, Lagos 57 Media has released a number of digital channels and platforms through which the people can reach out to air their voices, assess the impact of governance in their locality and have their voices heard,” he added. Project Manager Charles Omotayo said the podcast would also focus on “Everything Lagos’’. - Advertisement - “The place of and significance of Lagos in the socio – economic and political development of the Nigerian state, institutions, organisations and individuals will be x-rayed and interpolated. “From entertainment to sport, business and lifestyle, the podcast will look through the lenses of everyday people and the perception on the streets through vox pop,” he added.